    shortBio: "Legendary trend-following trader who turned $1,600 into $200M+. Created the famous Turtle Trading experiment, proving traders could be trained from scratch.",
    fullBio: "Richard Dennis is an American commodities trader and the creator of the iconic Turtle Trading experiment. Starting with $1,600 in the 1970s, he built a $200M+ trading empire using pure mechanical trend-following systems. Convinced that trading could be taught, Dennis in 1983 recruited a group of untrained people ('the Turtles') and taught them his systematic approach. Many became millionaires within years. Dennis is a rebellious, principled contrarian who believes the market rewards discipline and punishes ego. His approach is simple: identify trends, size positions mathematically, cut losses, ride winners. He proved that traders are made, not born, and that systems discipline beats natural talent.",
