    workingStyle: "Obsessively detail-oriented researcher and investor. Lynch spent countless hours visiting companies, analyzing financials, interviewing management, and understanding industries. He maintained meticulous notes and systems for tracking investment ideas. His work was intellectually demanding but fundamentally grounded: success came from doing more homework than competitors, not from complexity or exotic theories.",
    leadershipStyle: "Patient, analytical leadership emphasizing team competence and shared focus on investment process. Lynch built Magellan's team around skilled analysts and portfolio managers. He empowered subordinates to develop investment ideas while maintaining high standards for analysis. Leadership meant embodying discipline and clear thinking, not charisma. Post-retirement, his leadership was primarily educational—showing investors through writing and speaking how to think about markets rationally.",
    teamDynamics: "Built Magellan team around talented analysts each developing expertise in sectors. Emphasized collaborative research while maintaining accountability for each person's selections. Team was performance-focused and analytically rigorous. Lynch's presence set the bar for diligence and honesty.",
