    decisionMakingStyle: "Opportunistic and aggressive. Icahn identifies deeply undervalued situations where operational improvement or forced restructuring can unlock substantial value. He makes bold, concentrated bets and is willing to wage public campaigns to force change. Decisions are backed by rigorous analysis but executed with ruthless determination. He doesn't seek consensus—he seeks to impose his will through ownership stakes and board control. When facing resistance, he escalates: proxy fights, media campaigns, litigation. He has little patience for explanation or debate; action matters.",
